SpeciesName: combined limit for all shark and ray species
Description:
small to large bottom dwelling sharks
flattened head and body
numerous dermal lobes around the head and elaborate colouration

Tasselled wobbegong
dense tassel of dermal lobes around the head
blotches form a complex mosaic pattern

Spotted wobbegong
dark saddles superimposed and bordered by white rings and blotches

Northern wobbegong
smaller species
three large pale edged, dark blotches along the back and dark bands under each dorsal fin and above the anal fin

Banded wobbegong
dark saddles with white rings and blotches highlighted by black edges
two supraocular knobs above the eyes and four to six dermal lobes at the preocular group

Ornate wobbegong
similar to the banded wobbegong but smaller, more freckled and lacking supraocular knobs
three (rarely four) dermal lobes at the preocular group
